"How about my heart?" asked the Tin Woodman.
"Why, as for that,' answered Oz, "I think you are wrong
to want a heart. It makes most people unhappy. If you
only knew it, you are in luck not to have a heart."
"That must be a matter of opinion," said the Tin Wood-
man. "For my part, I will bear all the unhappiness with-
out a murmur, if you will give me the heart."
